div.p:
There is a strong consensus on our basic objectives. They are widely understood
                    and supported by the American people. I think all of us can agree that we serve
                    the interests of the United States best when we seek to: 

Protect the safety of our nation against aggression and subversion;

Promote our domestic prosperity;

Foster the values of freedom and democracy both at home and abroad;

Act in a manner consistent with our humanitarian instincts; and

Combat those activities which undermine the rule of law and our
                            domestic stability—particularly, right now, terrorism and narcotics
                            trafficking.
